description: The Spellmans turn their home into a bed and breakfast for Greendale's bicentennial celebration, and purge the house of magic so the guests aren't spooked. But they also banish the Spirit Shield and an imprisoned ghost gets let out of his closet.
name: House Arrest

description: Rotunda the troll masquerades as a foreign exchange student, imprisons Sabrina's family and sends Sabrina to take her place in the Nether Realm Juvenile Detention Center for Girls.
name: Troll Collector

description: Sabrina loses an earring on the beach, and it's found by someone with a metal detector. Turns out the earrings were a gift from Granny Gargle, who uses the earrings to keep tabs on Sabrina, and who is not happy that someone took it.
name: Now Ear This!

description: Sabrina ends up in a cast, then makes it worse when she tries to fix things magically. While wheelchair-bound she meets a new friend and discovers that the park is not friendly to handicapped people and decides to do something about it.
name: Foot Fault

description: Sabrina makes the cheerleading squad but learns that her handicapped friend Maggie isn't allowed to try out for her school's team. Maggie and Sabrina confront the team captain, who sics the football team on Sabrina. Friendship and good sportsmanship win the day.
name: Cheer Up!

description:
Based on the animated series airing on the ABC and UPN networks! "What a Charm-ing Cat": Salem figures a good-luck amulet is the best 'pawn' he can use as he faces off against Sabrina in chess. But this is one of Salem's plans, so before it's through, he's sure to get 'crowned!'

Gem runs for class president, and Sabrina joins the race to eliminate corruption. Gem gets Sabrina's "magic paintbrush" and ends up looking like a fool in front of the school.
name: Campaign in the Neck

description: Sabrina wants to help with Aunt Zelda's love life, but Cupid goes on strike and Sabrina briefly fills in, learning it's not as easy a job as it seems.
name: A Cupid Question
Black and white and dead all over!

description: Collects O-Men 0, 1 and 2.
name: Book One: Little Earthquakes

description: Collects O-Men 3 through 6.
name: Book Two: Frenzy

description: Collects O-Men 7 through 9.
name: Book Three: Malice

description: Collects O-Men 10 through 12.
name: Book Four: Tricks

description: Collects O-Men 13 through 15.
name: Book Five: Reunion

description: Collects O-Men 16 through 18.
name: Book Six: Confrontations

description: Collects O-Men 19 through 21.
name: Book Seven: Lies and Secrets

description: Collects O-Men 22 through 24.
name: Book Eight: Debris

description: Collects O-Men 25 through 27.
name: Book Nine: The Vicious Circle

description: Collects O-Men Season Two issues 2.1 through 2.3
name: Season Two, Book One: "Getting Back Together"

description: Mr. Monster plays host as he presents three classic horror stories.

"Practicing Her Scales!": Sabrina doesn't want to compete with his pet lizard for Harvey's affections, so attempts to conjure up an awesome lizard of her own... and accidentally turns herself into one in the process!

Sabrina wins cruise tickets and the aunts share time with her on board, and Salem is a stowaway. The Bahama Quadrangle causes some excitement but the time share salesman is worse.
name: Cruise Control

description: Doc Stearn introduces three incredible true and gritty stories by all-time great Jack Cole!
Doc Stearn hosts his second issue of rare true crime stories by all-great Jack Cole!
Includes strips on Joe 90, The Champions, Land of the Giants and Star Trek.

Journey with a select group of Earth`s Mightiest Heroes as they embark on a quest of cosmic proportions! When the Celestial Madonna known as Mantis sends out a space-spanning SOS that is received by the Vision, the Avengers` resident android gathers an elite unit of heroes - including Thor, Scarlet Witch, and Silverclaw - to come to her rescue. But what happens when the big bad gunning for Mantis turns out to be the nigh-omnipotent (and Death`s main squeeze) Thanos of Titan? Why, a galactic-sized dose of stellar excitement, brought to you as only Marvel Comics can bring it! Collecting CELESTIAL QUEST #1-8
name: TPB

description: The initial issue of the volume contains more than 6 different stories that are Halloween or monster themed. It also includes a reprinted Sabrina story from 1962 - the first appearance, from Madhouse #22.
name: Sabrina's Halloween Spook-tacular

description:
The second issue in the series has Sabrina saving Thanksgiving, Christmas and New Year's from the meddling of cranky Della the head witch.

Story #1 - Holi Dazed & Confused

Story #2 - Yule Yow

Story #3 - Hanging Hang Up

Story #4 - Photo Fun

Story #5 - Concrete Thinking

Story #6 - True To Type
name: Sabrina's Holiday Spectacular

description: Sabrina turns Salem into a young man so she can go to the Halloween dance with him. [Interestingly, Salem is orange in this issue.] At the dance he meets a girl, but is changed back into a cat. He convinces Sabrina to change him back at Christmas, because he'd made a date with Clarisse, who turns out to be a cat, as well. There are a few Christmas-themed stories and a New Year's story as well.
name: Holiday Spectacular

description: In the next issue of Meat Cake, Friend the Girl goes off to start an apiary and study under Dr. Granny (also a known beekeeper). Hold your horses for another fairy tale of equine proportions as Dame Darcy delights in 'Ghost Filly' and more murderous rage fills the short stories than you can shake an already-bloodied stick at!

person_credits.name: Dame Darcy
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover
